bug.summary: tf.unstack causes AttributeError: 'list' object has no attribute 'sym_type'
bug.description:
<denchmark-h:h2>üêûDescribe the bug</denchmark-h>
if tf.unstack is used, coremltools will show AttributeError: 'list' object has no attribute 'sym_type' converter: tensorflow
<denchmark-h:h2>Trace</denchmark-h>
<denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4080524/89099717-e63e2e00-d423-11ea-86a0-16e28a93d6b2.jpg></denchmark-link>
<denchmark-h:h2>To Reproduce</denchmark-h>
If a python script can reproduce the error, please paste the code snippet
import tensorflow as tf import tensorflow.keras.layers as layers import tensorflow.keras as keras
class stackTest(layers.Layer): def __init__(self, initializer="he_normal", **kwargs): super(stackTest, self).__init__(**kwargs) self.initializer = keras.initializers.get(initializer)
def call(self, inputs): x1, x2, x3, x4 = tf.unstack(inputs, axis=1) return tf.stack([x1, x2, x3, x4])
inputT = tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(1, )) dense = tf.keras.layers.Dense(4)(inputT) stack = stackTest()(dense)
model = tf.keras.models.Model(inputs=[inputT], outputs=[stack])
model.summary() import coremltools as ct coreml_model = ct.convert(model, source="tensorflow") <denchmark-h:h2>System environment (please complete the following information):</denchmark-h>
coremltools version (e.g., 3.0b5): 4.0b2 OS (e.g., MacOS, Linux): MacOS macOS version (if applicable): Big Sur beta 3 XCode version (if applicable): Xcode 11 How you install python (anaconda, virtualenv, system): anaconda python version (e.g. 3.7): 3.7 any other relevant information:
TensorFlow 2.2

comments.comment: From the code, it looks like you created the structure of the Keras model, then didn't compile it or train it and then proceeded to convert the untrained / uncompiled model to a coreml model.

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/ryendu>@ryendu</denchmark-link> It doesn't matter if I compile it or not The following model isn't compiled but it converts to CoreML model successfully. <denchmark-code>import coremltools as ct import tensorflow as tf import tensorflow.keras.layers as layers import tensorflow.keras as keras
inputT = tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(1, )) dense = tf.keras.layers.Dense(4)(inputT)
model = tf.keras.models.Model(inputs=[inputT], outputs=[dense])
model.summary()
coreml_model = ct.convert(model, source="tensorflow")
</denchmark-code>
The following model failed even though it has been compiled <denchmark-code>import coremltools as ct import tensorflow as tf import tensorflow.keras.layers as layers import tensorflow.keras as keras
